HEADWORD: Silicle
<hw>Sil"i*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>silicula</ets>, dim. of <ets>siliqua</ets> a pod or husk: cf. F.
<ets>silicule</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A seed vessel
resembling a silique, but about as broad as it is long. See
<er>Silique</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

